.SH NAME
Linux::Event::Reactor::Backend \- Contract for readiness backends used by Linux::Event::Reactor
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This module documents the contract implemented by readiness backends for
Linux::Event::Reactor.
.PP
A reactor backend owns the kernel registration and wait mechanism. The reactor
engine owns watcher replacement policy, timer integration, dispatch order,
signal integration, wakeups, and pidfd policy.
.PP
Backends are duck\-typed, but they are expected to implement the method surface
and callback semantics documented here.
.SH "REQUIRED METHODS"
.IX Header "REQUIRED METHODS"
.SS new(%args)
.IX Subsection "new(%args)"
Construct the backend object.
.SS \fBname()\fP
.IX Subsection "name()"
Return a short backend name such as \f(CW\*(C`epoll\*(C'\fR.
.ie n .SS "watch($fh, $mask, $cb, %opt)"
.el .SS "watch($fh, \f(CW$mask\fP, \f(CW$cb\fP, \f(CW%opt\fP)"
.IX Subsection "watch($fh, $mask, $cb, %opt)"
Register readiness interest for \f(CW$fh\fR and return the integer file descriptor.
.PP
The callback ABI is:
.PP
.Vb 1
\&  $cb\->($loop, $fh, $fd, $mask, $tag)
.Ve
.PP
Where \f(CW$loop\fR and \f(CW$tag\fR come from \f(CW%opt\fR if provided.
.SS unwatch($fh_or_fd)
.IX Subsection "unwatch($fh_or_fd)"
Remove an existing registration. Return true if a registration was removed.
.ie n .SS "run_once($loop, $timeout_s = undef)"
.el .SS "run_once($loop, \f(CW$timeout_s\fP = undef)"
.IX Subsection "run_once($loop, $timeout_s = undef)"
Enter the backend wait once, dispatch native readiness callbacks, and return the
number of processed events when available.
.SH "OPTIONAL METHODS"
.IX Header "OPTIONAL METHODS"
.ie n .SS "modify($fh_or_fd, $mask, %opt)"
.el .SS "modify($fh_or_fd, \f(CW$mask\fP, \f(CW%opt\fP)"
.IX Subsection "modify($fh_or_fd, $mask, %opt)"
Update an existing registration without a delete\-and\-add cycle. The reactor can
fall back to \f(CW\*(C`unwatch\*(C'\fR plus \f(CW\*(C`watch\*(C'\fR when this method is absent.
.SH "READINESS MASKS"
.IX Header "READINESS MASKS"
The reactor uses these bit flags:
.PP
.Vb 8
\&  READABLE => 0x01
\&  WRITABLE => 0x02
\&  PRIO     => 0x04
\&  RDHUP    => 0x08
\&  ET       => 0x10
\&  ONESHOT  => 0x20
\&  ERR      => 0x40
\&  HUP      => 0x80
.Ve
.PP
The backend is responsible for translating between these masks and the native
kernel representation.
.SH "CALLBACK RULES"
.IX Header "CALLBACK RULES"
Backend callbacks may run inline from \f(CW\*(C`run_once\*(C'\fR. That is normal for the
reactor model.
.PP
A backend must not reinterpret watcher policy. In particular, it must not
change the dispatch order chosen by the reactor engine.
.SH "FILEHANDLE OWNERSHIP"
.IX Header "FILEHANDLE OWNERSHIP"
A reactor backend observes filehandles. It does not take ownership of them.
Closing a filehandle remains the caller\*(Aqs responsibility.
